rComments: If this man needed a kidney transplant I would get tested to see if I was a match. He is so sweet and such a great prof. As long as you do the practice questions it should be very easy to succeed in his class. He's also so generous in his grading.

This man is an absolute sweetheart. A real gem, if you get the opportunity to choose him CHOOSE HIM. He is so down to earth, & is a real friend to the students he also explains his lectures in an informative way & his lectures are nice to watch. He also goes through problems and answers questions he is a very amazing guy. But DO THE WORK & PRACTICE

Dr. Mayer explains things well and is pretty fair to students. He has practice questions available and no assignments, just two midterms and a final (not much time for either though). Only complaint is he doesn't always write out the formula he's using. Doesn't respond quickly to emails.

I love this guy. I might've only barely passed chemistry (or not at all, we'll see how this exam goes), but Mayer is legitimately a great guy. Explains concepts well, has a clear passion for the course, and gives lots of practice for homework. Definitely stay on top of things though, and make sure you REALLY understand the material!

I made this account just to give him a good review. He is conversational and gets through the material. It's not an easy A, but he tells you exactly what you have to do to get there. I highly recommend him for any CHM courses!
